sequenceDiagram
    participant User as Data Scientist
    participant Dashboard as ODH Dashboard
    participant KubeAuthProxy as kube-auth-proxy
    participant LLMISVCCtrl as KServe llmisvc-controller
    participant ODHModelCtrl as odh-model-controller
    participant Gateway as data-science-gateway<br/>(Envoy)
    participant EPP as Gateway API Inference<br/>Extension (EPP)
    participant WVA as Workload Variant<br/>Autoscaler
    participant vLLM as vLLM / llm-d<br/>Worker Pods
    participant S3 as S3 Storage
    participant Client as External Client

    Note over User,Client: Workflow 1: LLM Inference via LLMInferenceService

    %% Deployment phase
    User->>Dashboard: Login via OIDC/OAuth
    Dashboard->>KubeAuthProxy: Auth delegation
    KubeAuthProxy-->>Dashboard: Authenticated session
    Dashboard-->>User: Show model serving UI

    User->>Dashboard: Create LLMInferenceService CR<br/>(model, GPU reqs, scaling policy)
    Dashboard->>LLMISVCCtrl: LLMInferenceService CR created

    LLMISVCCtrl->>LLMISVCCtrl: Reconcile: create LeaderWorkerSet,<br/>InferencePool, ScaledObjects
    LLMISVCCtrl->>WVA: Create WVA ScaledObject
    LLMISVCCtrl->>ODHModelCtrl: Trigger reconciliation

    ODHModelCtrl->>Gateway: Create HTTPRoute on<br/>data-science-gateway
    ODHModelCtrl->>ODHModelCtrl: Create EnvoyFilter<br/>for ext-proc integration
    ODHModelCtrl->>ODHModelCtrl: Create AuthPolicy,<br/>ServiceMonitor

    Note over vLLM: Pods start, pull image from registry.redhat.io
    vLLM->>S3: Download model artifacts<br/>(HTTPS/443, AWS IAM)

    %% Inference phase
    Client->>Gateway: POST /v1/chat/completions<br/>(HTTPS/443, TLS termination)
    Gateway->>EPP: ext-proc callback (gRPC)<br/>Filter -> Score -> Pick
    EPP->>EPP: KV-cache-aware scoring,<br/>prefix cache affinity
    EPP-->>Gateway: Selected backend pod
    Gateway->>vLLM: Forward request (HTTP)
    vLLM->>vLLM: Run LLM inference
    vLLM-->>Gateway: Streaming completion response
    Gateway-->>Client: SSE stream (HTTPS)

    %% Autoscaling
    WVA->>vLLM: Monitor saturation metrics
    WVA->>WVA: Queueing-theory-based<br/>replica calculation
    WVA->>LLMISVCCtrl: Adjust InferencePool replicas

