sequenceDiagram
    participant User as Data Scientist
    participant Dashboard as ODH Dashboard
    participant Gateway as data-science-gateway
    participant KubeAuthProxy as kube-auth-proxy
    participant ODHNotebook as odh-notebook-controller
    participant KFNotebook as upstream notebook-controller
    participant Notebook as Notebook Pod<br/>(JupyterLab)
    participant Feast as Feast Feature Server
    participant DSP as DS Pipelines
    participant MLflow as MLflow Tracking
    participant S3 as S3 Storage

    Note over User,S3: Workflow 3: Interactive Development (Notebook Workbench)

    User->>Dashboard: Create Data Science Project<br/>(select image, resources, data connections)
    Dashboard->>ODHNotebook: Create Notebook CR

    ODHNotebook->>ODHNotebook: Create StatefulSet,<br/>inject kube-rbac-proxy sidecar,<br/>configure OAuth annotations
    ODHNotebook->>KFNotebook: Delegate pod lifecycle

    KFNotebook->>Notebook: Create pod,<br/>mount data connections as env vars
    KFNotebook->>KFNotebook: Configure idle culling<br/>(kubeflow-resource-stopped)

    Dashboard->>Gateway: Create HTTPRoute for<br/>notebook URL path
    Gateway->>Gateway: Configure TLS termination

    User->>Gateway: Access notebook URL<br/>(HTTPS/443)
    Gateway->>KubeAuthProxy: Auth delegation
    KubeAuthProxy->>KubeAuthProxy: OIDC/OAuth auth +<br/>SubjectAccessReview
    KubeAuthProxy-->>Gateway: Authorized
    Gateway-->>Notebook: Forward to JupyterLab

    Note over Notebook: User develops ML code

    Notebook->>S3: Download training data<br/>(HTTPS, AWS IAM)
    Notebook->>Feast: Fetch feature vectors<br/>(HTTP/6566)
    Notebook->>Notebook: Train model locally
    Notebook->>MLflow: Log experiment metrics<br/>(HTTP/5000)
    Notebook->>S3: Upload model artifacts
    Notebook->>DSP: Submit pipeline run<br/>(HTTP/8888)

